erations, it might affect resource call sites, though JVM handles it. Is that necessary? It might be safer. I’m also cautious about using dynamic-class-loading for usual reflection. Class.forName does involve reflection but is used for class loading, and I think that's okay. Native could throw `UnsupportedFeatureError`, but tests shouldn't fail with correct unsupported cases. I need to import `org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport`.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_iscKwqaZnzLjCK5qPozYT3n7|fc_0a6e7474391d17770169f5a547d29881949113616756631128", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.codehaus.groovy/groovy-all/2.3.6/src/test/groovy/org_codehaus_groovy/groovy_all/GeneratedBytecodeAwareGroovyClassLoaderTest.groovy", "edits": [{"oldText": "import groovy.lang.GroovyClassLoader\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n", "newText": "import groovy.lang.GroovyClassLoader\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n"}, {"oldText": "public class GeneratedBytecodeAwareGroovyClassLoaderTest {\n    @Test\n    void generatedClassLoaderBridgeMethodsDelegateToSuperclassImplementations() {\n        GeneratedBytecodeAwareGroovyClassLoader loader = new GeneratedBytecodeAwareGroovyClassLoader(new GroovyClassLoader())\n        String missingResourceName = 'org/codehaus/groovy/groovy-all/generated-bytecode-aware-loader-test-resource.txt'\n\n        Class<?> classFromGeneratedHelper = GeneratedBytecodeAwareGroovyClassLoader.'class$'(GeneratedBytecodeAwareGroovyClassLoader.name)\n        Class<?> missingLoadedClass = loader.'super$2$findLoadedClass'('org.codehaus.groovy.groovy_all.NotLoadedByThisClassLoader')\n        Class<?> systemClass = loader.'super$2$findSystemClass'('java.lang.String')\n        URL missingResource = loader.'super$2$getResource'(missingResourceName)\n        Enumeration<URL> missingResources = loader.'super$2$getResources'(missingResourceName)\n\n        assertThat(classFromGeneratedHelper).isSameAs(G